---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Polar Manufacturing — Customer Story — Formic"
  description="Polar Manufacturing has made door and truck-body hardware since 1915 — on a 50-year-old press it runs by hand. With Formic, it automated that legacy line to 800 parts a shift, with no high upfront cost."
  ogTitle="Polar Manufacturing — Formic Customer Story"
  ogDescription="800 parts/shift · 80 parts/hour · legacy press automated"
>
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://formic.co/stories/polar-manufacturing" slot="head" />

<div class="detail-bc">
  <a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span><a href="/stories">Customer Stories</a><span class="sep">/</span>Polar Manufacturing
</div>

<section class="detail-hero">
  <div class="si">
    <div class="slabel" style="color:var(--orange)">Customer Story · Polar Manufacturing</div>
    <h1 style="font-size:clamp(32px,3.8vw,56px)">Polar Manufacturing and Formic Partner to Overcome Legacy Equipment Challenges and Boost Productivity</h1>
    <p class="lede">Polar Manufacturing has made door and truck-body hardware since 1915 — on a 50-year-old press it still runs by hand. With Formic, it automated that legacy line to 800 parts a shift, with no high upfront cost.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dark">
  <div class="detail-video wide">
    <div class="detail-video-frame">
      <img src="/stories/polar-manufacturing-hero.jpg" alt="Polar Manufacturing automated press tending cell" />
      <span class="dv-cap">Polar Manufacturing · since 1915</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white" style="padding:64px 0 0">
  <div class="si" style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 80px">
    <div class="db-tag">At a glance</div>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(150px,1fr));gap:1px;background:var(--lgrey);border:1px solid var(--lgrey);margin-top:14px">
      <div style="background:var(--white);padding:18px 20px"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mgrey);margin-bottom:6px">Founded</div><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:17px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black)">1915</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--white);padding:18px 20px"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mgrey);margin-bottom:6px">Ownership</div><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:17px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black)">Family-owned</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--white);padding:18px 20px"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mgrey);margin-bottom:6px">Industry</div><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:17px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black)">Door & truck-body hardware</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--white);padding:18px 20px"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mgrey);margin-bottom:6px">The press</div><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:17px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black)">~50 years old</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--white);padding:18px 20px"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mgrey);margin-bottom:6px">Output</div><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:17px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black)">800 parts/shift</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white">
  <div class="db-grid">
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">01 — The Challenge</div>
      <h2>Automating a press <em>older than most of the team</em>.</h2>
      <p>Polar Manufacturing has designed and made door and truck-body hardware since 1915 — and still runs a roughly 50-year-old press by hand. It turned to Formic to automate without high upfront costs, in a sector where 98% of US manufacturing employment sits in small and medium firms, and the largest manufacturers run 58% higher labor productivity than their mid-sized peers.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Making hardware since 1915</li>
        <li>A ~50-year-old press, still run manually</li>
        <li>Competing against far larger, more productive firms</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/stories/polar-manufacturing-2.jpg" alt="Polar Manufacturing robotic press-tending cell" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Legacy press · automated</span></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block lgrey">
  <div class="db-grid flip">
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/MachineTending-CNC.jpg" alt="UR5e robot tending a legacy press" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">UR5e · custom cell</span></div>
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">02 — The Solution</div>
      <h2>A cell built <em>around the old press</em>.</h2>
      <p>With integrator Designhawk, Formic built a cell around a UR5e robot, two jaw grippers, a touch-screen HMI, stand wheels, an input magazine, and an automated oiling mechanism. The hard engineering got solved: external sensors to detect the 50-year-old press, a mobile system for multiple part types, and an automated safety block for the bending operation.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>UR5e robot, grippers, touch-screen HMI, auto-oiling</li>
        <li>External sensors to read the legacy press</li>
        <li>Mobile system handles multiple part types</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white" style="padding:88px 80px">
  <div class="si" style="max-width:900px;margin:0 auto;padding:0">
    <div class="pull-quote">
      <blockquote>"If Polar didn't automate, Polar would not be in business. We cannot compete if we cannot produce."</blockquote>
      <cite>Jose Figueroa · Plant Manager, Polar Manufacturing</cite>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dark">
  <div class="si" style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;padding:80px;text-align:center">
    <div class="db-tag" style="justify-content:center">03 — The Impact</div>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:clamp(40px,5vw,72px);font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.02em;line-height:1;color:var(--white);margin:18px 0 56px">Legacy line, <em style="color:var(--orange);font-style:normal">modern output.</em></h2>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:1px;background:rgba(255,255,255,.1)">
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:36px 24px"><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:48px;font-weight:500;color:var(--orange);line-height:1">800</div><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(240,245,241,.55);margin-top:12px">Parts per 10-hour shift</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:36px 24px"><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:48px;font-weight:500;color:var(--orange);line-height:1">80</div><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(240,245,241,.55);margin-top:12px">Parts per hour</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:36px 24px"><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:48px;font-weight:500;color:var(--orange);line-height:1">1915</div><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(240,245,241,.55);margin-top:12px">Making hardware since</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-cta">
  <h2>Modernize your <em>legacy line</em>.</h2>
  <div class="btn-row">
    <a href="mailto:sales@formic.co" class="btn-ctadark">Get Started</a>
    <a href="/stories" class="btn-ctawh">More Customer Stories</a>
  </div>
</section>
</Layout>
